+{"id":"frankenpandas-derlf","title":"fd90.123: README df.pct_change() missing required periods: usize arg","description":"fd90.74-122 README audit. Line 1050 in Cumulative and Sequential section shows:

  let pct   = df.pct_change()?;  // Percentage change

But crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs:25118 declares:
  pub fn pct_change(&self, periods: usize) -> Result<Self, FrameError>

DataFrame::pct_change requires periods: usize (the n-period lag for the change). A user copy-pasting hits:
  error[E0061]: this method takes 1 argument but 0 arguments were supplied

The Series variant at 5435 also takes periods: usize, so no overload rescues this.

Fix: pass periods = 1 (the pandas default) so the example actually compiles. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T11:32:13.731380880Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T11:33:23.087432253Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T11:33:23.084558278Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
